        "label": "Why It Matters",
        "headline": "Why 'Frankenstein' Skincare Fails",
        "body": "<p>When you build a 'Frankenstein' routine—piecing together a Vitamin C serum from Brand X and a Retinol from Brand Y—you are taking a significant risk with your skin's delicate acid mantle.</p><ol><li><strong>Ingredient Inactivation:</strong> Many active ingredients are highly unstable. Applying a high-strength AHA immediately before certain peptide serums can alter the pH so drastically that the peptides denature, rendering your expensive serum useless.</li><li><strong>Barrier Disruption:</strong> Layering multiple strong actives without the correct supporting lipids leads to transepidermal water loss and micro-inflammation — accelerating the very ageing process you're trying to prevent. This is known as 'inflammageing.'</li><li><strong>The Penetration Problem:</strong> Clinical-grade results require active ingredients to reach the deeper layers of the epidermis. A protocol is formulated with specific delivery systems to ensure active ingredients bypass the dead stratum corneum and reach the living cells where collagen is produced.</li></ol>",
        "bg": "white",
